&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apr 21 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experiments force us to acknowledge other universes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brett:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have to come to a deeper understanding of what is going on in this &lt;strong&gt;double-slit experiment&lt;/strong&gt;. If we fire either a photon or an electron at that double-slit apparatus and put a detector at either of those slits, then we will detect a particle.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Is Light a Particle or a Wave?</title><link>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/is-light-a-particle-or-a-wave/</link><pubDate>Mon, 19 Apr 2021 21:07:49 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/is-light-a-particle-or-a-wave/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguage.github.io/naval/zh/is-light-a-particle-or-a-wave.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
