&lt;h1 id="we-cant-prove-most-theorems-with-known-physics"&gt;We Can’t Prove Most Theorems with Known Physics&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Apr 14 2021&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unprovable theorems vastly outnumber the provable ones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brett:&lt;/strong&gt;
The overwhelming majority of theorems in mathematics are theorems that we cannot possibly prove. This is &lt;a href=""&gt;Gödel’s theorem&lt;/a&gt;, and it also comes out of &lt;a href=""&gt;Turing’s proof&lt;/a&gt; of what is and is not computable.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Every Theory Is Held Inside a Physical Substrate</title><link>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/every-theory-is-held-inside-a-physical-substrate/</link><pubDate>Mon, 12 Apr 2021 18:06:51 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/every-theory-is-held-inside-a-physical-substrate/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguage.github.io/naval/zh/every-theory-is-held-inside-a-physical-substrate.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
