&lt;h1 id="is-the-universe-discrete-or-continuous"&gt;Is the Universe Discrete or Continuous?&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apr 9 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Quantum theory and relativity disagree&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
You said that we went from atoms in the time of Democrates, down to nuclei, and from there to protons and neutrons, and then to quarks. It&amp;rsquo;s particles all the way down, to paraphrase Feynman. We can keep going forever. But it&amp;rsquo;s not quite forever, right? At some point you run into the Planck length.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>The Methods of Mathematics Are Fallible</title><link>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/the-methods-of-mathematics-are-fallible/</link><pubDate>Mon, 05 Apr 2021 19:22:30 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguage.github.io/naval/orig/the-methods-of-mathematics-are-fallible/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguage.github.io/naval/zh/the-methods-of-mathematics-are-fallible.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
